IV Functional all-around tournament "In Memory of Fallen Heroes" for the prizes of the head of the Main Directorate of the Ministry of Emergency Situations of Russia for the Leningrad Region, the Kolesnikov Team and the Russian Union of Rescuers, in memory of firefighters, rescuers, military personnel and employees of other law enforcement agencies who died in the line of duty. Competitive complexes will include: - body weight squats;
- jumping on a pedestal;
- push ups;
- burpees over the bar;
- lifting the body from a supine position;
- deadlift;
- kettlebell swings;
- dumbbell press;
- run;
- overcoming an obstacle course;
- tire traction/tilting;
- as well as other functional exercises for moving your own body or external objects. When? May 25, 2024 Where? Training base
test site of the North-Western regional search
rescue squad of the Ministry of Emergency Situations of Russia
Address: Leningrad region, Vsevolozhsk district, Murino,
Oboronnaya Street, 51. Online form for registration of participants: https://forms.gle/WG8kQSZguAEd6HE67VK: https://vk.com/turnir_ruorConditions: Men and women over 18 years old are allowed to participate.
Competitions are held in individual competition, in two categories: men and women.

Each participant is required to have an identification document, a compulsory medical insurance policy, an employee/employee ID of a fire and rescue unit, an emergency rescue unit and/or a voluntary fire and rescue unit, an ID of a rescuer and/or an employee of other law enforcement agencies.

Athletes are allowed to participate only if they have firefighter's combat clothing, a firefighter's helmet, a fire-rescue belt (without an ax and a carbine) and sports shoes. Employees of other law enforcement agencies are allowed to wear sports uniforms and have body armor (platinum) weighing at least 6 kilograms.

And this is a neutral flag, under which Russian and Belarusian athletes will be allowed to compete at the 2024 Olympics in Paris. The IOC has approved several more rules:
– their medals will not be added to the overall standings;
– awards will be presented not to anthems, but to music without words;
– our athletes will not be able to participate in the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games (they are still deciding on the closure). Subscribe to the media

